AGI - The military of the Provincial Command of the guard of finance of Genoa are giving execution to an order of application of precautionary measures (coercitive and interdittive) personal and real issued today from the gip of the Tribunal of Genoa, on request of the Procura deposited on 27 December to the president of the Liguria Region, Giovanni Toti, of Paolo Emilio Signorini, already president of the Harbour System Authority of the Western Ligurian Sea, The other recipients of the order > are Arturo Angelo Testa and Italo Maurizio Testa, and Venanzio Maurici. Mr.ini, investigated for corruption for the exercise of the function and for acts contrary to the duties of office, is the recipient of a measure of the precautionary custody in prison, while for Toti were arranged domicile arrests for the same crimes.&nbsp;
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
<h2>
Aldo Spinelli, entrepreneur in the logistic and real estate sector, for which the house arrests were taken, is disputed corruption against Signorini and Toti. For the entrepreneur Roberto Spinelli, to whom corruption is disputed against the President of the Region, the interim measure of the temporary prohibition of exercising business and professional activity has been arranged. The same precautionary measure for Mauro Vianello, an entrepreneur working in the field of the Port of Genoa, accused of corruption against Signorini; for Francesco Moncada, board of directors of Esselunga spa, which is disputed the same crime against Toti.<br> Matteo Cozzani, head of cabinet of the president of the Liguria Region, is under house arrest for 'election competition', aggravated by the hypothesis that the crime has been committed to facilitate the activity of the Mafia association Cosa Nostra, in particular of the Cammarata of Cozzani is also investigated for corruption for the exercise of the function.
&nbsp;
Arturo Angelo Testa and Italo Maurizio Testa, representatives of the Riesine community of Genoa, are recipients of the obligation to dwell in the Municipality of Boltiere, with the charge of exacerbated electoral corruption.<br> The same crime is challenged to Venanzio Maurici, recipient of the obligation to submit to the judicial police.
&nbsp;
<h2>Red, not excluding resigns
"Before expressing an assessment I wait to see the cards, read well and understand. Of course, this story has happened between our heads and necks, something like this would never have expected." Thus, Matteo Rosso, deputy and regional coordinator of Fratelli d'Italia in Liguria, comments with Affaritaliani.it the news of the house arrests of the president of the Giovanni Toti Region.
